rchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."]},{"name":"Nicolò","meanings":["feminine form of   Nicholas ."]},{"name":"Niccolò","meanings":["feminine form of   Nicholas ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":21,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":34,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":43,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Nicola Bardolf was born about 1294, in Drayton, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Sir Robert d'Arderne. She died in 1365, in Drayton, Berkshire, England, at the age of 72."},"et":{"Abt 1294–1365":"umbes 1294–1365","1240–1331":"1240–1331","1280–1314":"1280–1314","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1318–1379":"1318–1379","1330–1376":"1330–1376","1314–1360":"1314–1360","1294–1365":"1294–1365","Abt 1315":"umbes 1315","1330":"1330","1240":"1240","1294":"1294","1360":"1360","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","Abt 1294":"um